  "title": "Barn Door Cabinet with Hooks",
  "summary": "A tall entryway cabinet with a shop-built barn door, a divider splitting the case into two shelved bays, and a dedicated hook rail for coats — unlike this catalog's pantry and media barn-door pieces.",
  "description": "The carcass is a single tall case — two sides and a center divider, joined by eight shelves split across the two bays behind the door. **A dedicated hook support board is built into the case**, sized for mounting coat hooks, which is what makes this piece an entryway cabinet rather than a pantry or media unit — none of this catalog's other barn-door builds are designed around hanging coats.\n\nBuild the face frame around the carcass opening, then hang the barn door on its own separate frame using 48\" sliding barn door hardware (or shop-built hardware if preferred). The top, made from a 1x8 and 1x6 glued together, caps the whole case and gives it a finished, slightly deep profile.\n\nThe footer at the base is scribed and cut to fit your own floor, since an 84\"-tall case shows any gap at the bottom immediately. A full plywood back closes the case in from behind.",
